originalText.text: Don't be fooled by the amenities, especially the rooftop. While they advertise and try to impress people with the rooftop pool, there's NO benefit or discount whatsoever for the residents and requires absurd amount of membership fee for which you cannot even bring guests or drinks freely. No day passes, no other options unless you want to pay at least $1600 -$3200 in addition to the expensive rent which is not worth the money. Don't expect good service once you're in, since the staffs are arrogant and rude. One of the staffs unnecessarily yelled at me not to lean on the rail when he could've just told me nicely. They also continuously bring multiple groups of friends of their own which should not be happening since silver members are only allowed to bring 6 guests the whole year(yes the entire year). The rooftop also closes frequently to host private events, preventing members from using it. A lot of disappointment with this rooftop.

originalText.text:
Completely over priced, looks nothing like the pictures, the staff is rude, arrogant and bias.

This is not a welcoming friendly environment and they don’t have day passes available.

Memberships run from $1500-$3200 and even with a membership the rooftop is closed most of the time for private events.

These complaints have been expressed to management but they don’t care.

PLEASE DON’T WASTE YOUR TIME AND MONEY

originalText.text: The place is a little overpriced in my opinion and I was disappointed to see the venue. This was because when compared to the pictures I saw online, the area was much smaller. I guess that's just NYC. The three stars however dont do justice to the view, I would give it 5 stars if it wasn't for the price and its misleading pictures. The staff is friendly and the quality of service seems adequate. You should check it out for your instagram.
